                        <section>
                            <header>
                                <h2>Timesplitters</h2>
                                <span class="byline">My First Venture Into Level Editing</span>
                            </header>
                            <p>I was originally introduced to "Timesplitters 2" and following that "Timesplitters: Future Perfect" during my preadolescence by one of my friends and due to it's similarity to other games we played at the time it seamlessly transitioned into one of our regularly played games.</p>
                            <p>Now while as a group we found ourselves very much occupied by the standard campaign and arcade game modes (Virus, in particular, was one of my favorites) I personally believe that the Mapmaker effectively acted as life extension to the series as it allowed for custom maps to be played, tweaked and otherwise fresh content to be introduced. Due to this we produced a lot of maps in both "Timesplitters 2" and "Timesplitters: Future Perfect" - which fortunately due to its nature as a console game allowed the saves to survive to this day on a small collection of GameCube memory cards.</p>
                            <p>Whilst several other games at the time also fed my creative demons (Rollercoaster Tycoon 1/2, Transport Tycoon Deluxe etc.) all of my efforts within those games have been lost to the sands of time within several now-presumably-deceased and certainly-dumped HDD's. As a result of this "Timesplitters 2" and "Timesplitters: Future Perfect" hold the personal record of being host to some of the oldest things I have created that still currently exist and thanks to some Wii magic and an old website I have been able to move them and in some instances recreate them for your viewing and playing pleasure.</p>
                            <p>Anyhow, onto the finer details. While my old Timesplitters website still exists it has been officially shutdown as of 2014. As a result of this several of the HTML files that existed for "Timesplitters: Future Perfect" which were created in "Sturan's Mapmaker" needed a new home - several of these date back to early 2006 and as a result of this not all of them had save files and quite a few of the save files which did exist were heavily modified from the HTML versions due to being used for personal rather than public use as was the case with the HTML files... hence I've more or less had to migrate these files and then recreate saves based on the plans outlined in the HTML documents. A list of these can be found below.</p>
                            
                            <p><b>Timesplitters: Future Perfect:</b></p> 
                            
                            <ul>
                            <li>Big Easy, Big Easy 2 and Big Easy 3</li>
                            <li>Temple</li>
                            <li>Lab Run and Lab Run 2</li>
                            <li>Metro 163</li>
                            <li>Castle and Castle 2</li>
                            <li>Doom Tower</li>
                            <li>Tower</li>
                            <li>Elywof Mall</li>
                            <li>Hell Hole</li>
                            <li>Primesville</li>
                            <li>Subway</li>
                            <li>Dead Village</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>On the other side of the fence several "Timesplitters: Future Perfect" save files existed without the relevant HTML files to compliment them - up until now these have also only existed on my or my friends memory cards so it is quite nice to be able to share them and have them exist forevermore on something that is more stable than an easily lost GameCube memory card. A list of these "Timesplitters: Future Perfect" and "Timesplitters 2" saves can be found below.</p>
                            <p>(<b>Please Note:</b> Due to Sturan's Mapmaker software having been effectively abandoned by this point there is currently no and probably never going to be a version of this software which supports "Timesplitters 2" tiles, items and settings hence there are no HTML plans available for any of the "Timesplitters 2" saves.)</p>
                            
                            <p><b>Timesplitters 2:</b></p>
                            
                            <ul>
                            <li>Hell Hole, Hell Hole 2, Hell Hole 3, Hell Hole 4 and Hell Hole 5</li>
                            <li>Maxs World and Maxs World 2</li>
